daily_routine: Each morning at 4 AM, Aput checks the ice conditions from his kitchen
  window with binoculars his grandfather gave him. He prepares his hunting gear out
  of habit - sealskin boots, harpoon, ice picks - then walks to the shore to find
  only dark water where ice should be. He spends hours at the community center's computer,
  checking satellite images of ice formation, hoping to find huntable conditions somewhere
  within dog sled range. Afternoons, he teaches traditional ice-reading skills to
  children who will likely never use them.
